<div class="page">

  <div class="page-header">
    <h1>Borrowing Against Your Stack</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">A supplemental retirement framework &mdash; using bitcoin as collateral instead of selling it.</p>
  </div>

  <div style="text-align: center;">
    <span class="cs-badge">Phase 3.5 &mdash; coming soon</span>
  </div>

  <div class="cs-content">

    <p class="stub-prose">Borrowing against your bitcoin stack uses the asset as collateral for a loan, the proceeds of which fund retirement income. The bitcoin itself is not sold &mdash; the appeal is that the stack continues to compound under the Power Law while the loan provides liquid spending power. The trade is real: instead of triggering taxable sales, you accrue interest, and the loan principal eventually has to be repaid. For most users, that repayment ultimately comes from the stack itself, which is why the strategy is structurally a <em>tactical modifier</em> on sell-as-needed rather than a peer alternative.</p>

    <p class="stub-prose">This page is in active development. It will carry its own framing essay, an interactive risk surface (loan-to-value ratios, liquidation prices, interest-rate compounding, the percentage of stack borrowed), and a slider that lets you see what 0% borrowing looks like as the genuinely conservative baseline. The framework deserves a full canvas rather than a corner of the foundational calculator &mdash; both because the cognitive load (LTV, liquidation, interest) is meaningfully heavier and because the cultural load (the <em>&ldquo;never sell&rdquo;</em> mythology, the recent failures of overleveraged borrowing platforms) demands editorial care.</p>

    <p class="stub-prose">For the foundational retirement framework &mdash; sell as needed &mdash; return to the primary calculator.</p>

